{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-09-07","name":"Ralph de Coggeshall","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Ralph de Coggeshall","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Ralph"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Coggeshall"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Ralph de Coggeshale","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1213–1305","fullLifespan":"Abt 1213–Abt 1305","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7756-107692-4398-66/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/126638808","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7756-107692-4398-66/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7756-107692-4398-66/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7748-107692-4205-82/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/126638809","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7748-107692-4205-82/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7748-107692-4205-82/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7756-107692-4399-71/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/126638810","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7756-107692-4399-71/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7756-107692-4399-71/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Abbey of Tilty.","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1213","birthPlace":{"address":"Essex, England","geo":{"latitude":51.85229,"longitude":0.61466,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1305","deathPlace":{"address":"Essex, England","geo":{"latitude":51.85229,"longitude":0.61466,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Biography\nSir Ralph de Coggeshall of Codham Hall, Wethersfield, Essex, England, living 1233. He was married to Elizabeth Codham. They had a son John, who died in 1296. \n\nSir Ralph held 1.5 fees in manors of Pakelesham, Codham, Dodenhoo and Coggesfale, all in Essex. Ralph died circa 1305.\n\nRalph de Coggleshell who held Codam Hall in Wethersfield, died in 1305, held this manor partly of John Filial and partly of the abbots of Coggeshall and Westminster, and of William Atte Napelton. His son [grandson] and heir John de Coggeshell held estates here in 1319 at the time of his decease and the same were held by John, his son, in 1361. \n\nHe married Elizabeth (enfeoffment of Ralph de Coggeshall and Elizabeth his wife, manor of Duddenhoe, for life, 17 July 1279.\n\nWhose Ralph's Father?\nRalph has been identified as the son of Lawrence Coggeshal, yet other sources give his father as Sir Thomas Coggeshall, living 1188 and 1194. \n\nThree records identify his father as Lawrence.\n\n46 Henry III (1261-1262), p 250: 1488. Ralph, son of Laurence deCoggeshall, dem. Richard Abbot of Westminster, ten., by Richard de Naylingeherst. 9 acres of land with appurts in Ferynge. Dem. quitclaimed to ten. quitchaimed to dem 4s. of yearly rent with appurts. which dem. previously used to render to him for the pond of the mill called Poyntelemelne in the town of Coggeshall.' Moreover ten. gave to dem. 1 mark of silver.\n\n\"12 November 1279 at Westminster: confirmation of a grant in frank almoin which the King has inspected, made by Ralph son of Laurence de Coggeshal to the church of St Mary, Coggeshal, and the monks there, of the whole tenement which he had in the town of Markeshal of the gift of Herbert de Markeshal\"\n\n15 Edward I (1286-1287) 388. Trin. \"Ralph, son of Laurence de Cogeshale, pl. Robert, son of John Baard of Aldebyry and Felicia his wife, impedients. 2 messuages, 1 mill, 260 acres of land, 16 acres of meadow, 32 acres of pasture, 18s. of rent, 9 1/2 acres of wood in Elmedone and Arkesdene. Plea of Warrenty of charter. Pl. to hold of impedients and heirs of Felicia by the yearly rent of 1d. at Easter, doing other services to the chief lords.----\"\n\nRalph and Laurence de Plumbergh, father-in-law of Ralph's son John\n\"4 Edward I: Ralph de Coggeshal to grant land at Markshall to the abbot and convent of Coggeshall, Essex\" (1275/6) IPM: Ralph de Cokeshale alias Coggeshale alias Goggeshale: writ 4 May 33 Edward I: Inquests, Essex, 18-24 May 33 Ed I: Little Bemflet:: messuage and land held for life only of Laurence de Plumbergh, granted to the said Ralph, John his son and Sarra wife of the said John, now deceased, to them and the heirs of the said Sarra; Pakelesham: manor held with John his son and Sarra the wife of the said John, to John and Sarra and the heirs of the said Sarra; Codham manor; Shaldeford; Dodenhoo manor; Coggeshale manor; heir: his son John, aged 26[elsewhere in IPM 'aged 30']\n\nIPM: Ralph de Cokeshale alias Coggeshale alias Goggeshale: writ 4 May 33 Edward I: Inquests, Essex, 18-24 May 33 Ed I: Little Bemflet: messuage and land held for life only of Laurence de Plumbergh, granted to the said Ralph, John his son and Sarra wife of the said John, now deceased, to them and the heirs of the said Sarra; Pakelesham: manor held with John his son and Sarra the wife of the said John, to John and Sarra and the heirs of the said Sarra; Codham manor; Shaldeford; Dodenhoo manor; Coggeshale manor; heir: his son John, aged 26 [elsewhere in IPM 'aged 30']","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1213","date":"Abt 1213","place":"Essex, Eng